<item>
            <title>[PIG-3191] MultiStorage output filenames are not sortable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3191</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The MultiStorage output filenames are not properly sortable.&lt;br/&gt;
The output filenames do not pad the index, so the first split will be &lt;br/&gt;
xxxxx-0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as opposed to what the class documentation says, which is &lt;br/&gt;
xxxxx-0000&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;When retrieving these files the sorted order may not be as expected.&lt;/p&gt;


